It's always saddening to me to see someone, who has been tricked, defrauded by the world. Tragic. Back in the mountain villages here, men at weddings placed big bets on if the bride was virgin or not. I remember one man wagered an entire house once. Savage, brutal perennial rite.

The women entered the room, seized and displayed the bedsheets after consummation. If the man was a fool, and his bride was taken by another beforehand, he sometimes cut his finger with a knife and stained them with his own blood. A humiliation beyond belief. Nothing comes close.
